update

public void update(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                   File _file,
                   String _newVersion)
            throws Exception
Updates this administration (business) object if the stored information about the version is not the same as the file date. If an update is required, the file is read and the object is updated with update(ParameterCache_mxJPO, CharSequence, CharSequence, CharSequence, Map, File).

Specified by:
update in class AbstractObject_mxJPO
Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
_file - file with TCL update code
_newVersion - new version which must be set within the update (or null if the version must not be set).
Throws:
Exception - if the update from the derived class failed

extractSymbolicNameFromCode

private String extractSymbolicNameFromCode(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                                           StringBuilder _code)

Returns the symbolic name for current property object. If parameter PARAM_CALCSYMBOLICNAMES is defined, the symbolic name is only calculated. Otherwise the header is checked if there is a defined symbolic name (and by used if exists). A check is done if the symbolic name starts correctly with the administration type name (in lower case!). If not, the calculated symbolic name is used. A warning is shown if the symbolic name defined in the header is not equal to the calculated symbolic name.

The symbolic name is calculated by removing all spaces and slashes within the name of the object and add as prefix the administration type name.

Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
_code - TCL update source code
Returns:
extracted symbolic name from the source code header
See Also:
PARAM_CALCSYMBOLICNAMES

update

protected void update(ParameterCache_mxJPO _paramCache,
                      CharSequence _preMQLCode,
                      CharSequence _postMQLCode,
                      CharSequence _preTCLCode,
                      Map<String,String> _tclVariables,
                      File _sourceFile)
               throws Exception
The method updates this administration (business) object. First all MQL commands are concatenated:
  • pre MQL commands (from parameter _preMQLCode)
  • change to TCL mode
  • define the TCL logging procedures
  • set all required TCL variables (from parameter _tclVariables)
  • append TCL update code from file (from parameter _tclCode)
  • change back to MQL mode
  • append post MQL statements (from parameter _postMQLCode)
At the end of the MQL statements, TEST_EXECUTED is printed via MQL command "output so that this output is returned from the MQL execution. The return of the MQL execution is tested if this output is returned. If not an exception is thrown because the update failed.

Parameters:
_paramCache - parameter cache
_preMQLCode - MQL statements which must be called before the TCL code is executed
_postMQLCode - MQL statements which must be called after the TCL code is executed
_preTCLCode - TCL code which is defined before the source file is sourced
_tclVariables - map of all TCL variables where the key is the name and the value is value of the TCL variable (the value is automatically converted to TCL syntax!)
_sourceFile - souce file with the TCL code to update; if null file is not called (sourced)
Throws:
Exception - if update failed
See Also:
TCL_LOG_PROCS
